text:
bug on batik SVG DOM implementation on the SVGPathSegArcAbs & SVGPathSegArcRel

the SVGPathSegArc doesn't get the method getR1() & getR2() correctly, it return 0
after see the code the fix may be like below (based on batik 1.5beta5)

on the package org.apache.batik.dom.svg;

class AbstractSVGPathSegList.SVGPathSegArcItem

line 544 this.r1 = r1;  // suppose this.r1=rx;
line 545 this.r2 = r2;  // suppose this.r2=ry;

public SVGPathSegArcItem(short type,String letter,
                             float rx,float ry,float angle,
                             boolean largeArcFlag, boolean sweepFlag,
                             float x, float y ){
            super(type,letter);
            this.x = x;
            this.y = y;
            //this.r1 = r1;
            //this.r2 = r2;
            this.r1 = rx;
            this.r2 = ry;
            this.angle = angle;
            this.largeArcFlag = largeArcFlag;
            this.sweepFlag = sweepFlag;
        }
